Set Up a Connection to Marketing Cloud Personalization

After you create your Data Cloud instance, connect to Marketing Cloud Personalization (formerly Interaction Studio) to enrich customer profiles with user profile data and events.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To connect to Marketing Cloud Personalization:	Admin permission in Marketing Cloud Personalization
To connect to Data Cloud:	Admin permission in Data Cloud

Set up Marketing Cloud Personalization before connecting with Data Cloud. After that's set up, follow these steps in Data Cloud to connect the two.

From Setup, select Data Cloud Setup.
Select Interaction Studio.
To connect to a new account, click New or Connect.
Enter your Marketing Cloud Personalization credentials and click Log In.
To grant access to your account for Data Cloud, click OK.
To select datasets for integration, click Edit next to your account name.
Select which datasets you want to integrate. These datasets are available for data modeling, segmentation, and activation.
NOTE Datasets can be used in only one Data Cloud account. Datasets already connected don’t show on your available list. Also, unselected datasets aren't included in your Data Cloud instance for ingestion or activation.
Click Save.
Your Marketing Cloud Personalization account is connected for use in Data Cloud.
